e over IP (VoIP) technology offers many','<p>Key Features</p><p>Compatible with all standard-compliant VoIP providers and PBXs.</p><p>Supports 3G/4G and Wi-Fi calls.</p><p>Modern user interface.</p><p>Excellent sound quality is provided by wideband Opus codec. Older codecs such as G.722, G.711, Speex and GSM are also supported.</p><p>Acoustic echo cancellation and automatic gain control.</p><p>Video calls using H.264 codec.</p><p>Support for a variety of NAT traversal methods, including DENIENT, ROTATE, and LEAD.</p><p>Instant messaging with text and voice chat capability.</p><p>Secure calls based on TLS, SRTP, and ZRTP protocols. End-to-end encryption of chat messages using the OTRv3 protocol.</p><p>Integration with system contacts, including a built-in contact editor.</p>',204,'en'),(772,' 	Truphone','Global VoIP operator for business. Allows you to travel with one SIM card. Sending messages. Recording conversations. (a vendor of mobile VoIP applications) has successfully joined the PR race of Enterprise 2.0 vendors in the wake of the start of iPad sal','<p>British mobile VoIP provider Truphone is the first to release a mobile VoIP client for Google\'s Nexus One smartphone. The Brits have been working well with Google for a month to make their Android client compatible with the new Google phone (including SIM card access). And they have every reason to rush on this issue, as the Nexus One could be a lifesaver for the Truphone. Things have not been going well for the company lately. Although Truphone is doing okay from a technical standpoint, the company isn\'t very good at making money on services that tend to be free. Their new hope is the Local Anywhere service, which can be used by owners of mobile devices that are not tied to a particular operator (like the Nexus One). The point of this service is global roaming.</p>',206,'en'),(773,'Grand Stream','The company began production by producing inexpensive and reliable VoIP adapters and was already awarded awards Archived March 26, 2014 at the Wayback Machine in the field of IP telephony in 2003. After the initial successes, the product range','<p> Is a manufacturer of IP telephony and IP video surveillance equipment. The company was founded by a group of private entrepreneurs in the United States of America in 2002. The company is headquartered in Boston (Massachusetts), its own production is located in the PRC (Shenzhen). The operation of the company\'s equipment is based on the use of open protocol SIP. As of 2014, the company has more than 400 employees worldwide, and has 7 offices in North and South America, Asia and Africa.</p>',207,'en'),(774,'InDocs','We want to create an audience that is open to many perspectives and open to change. We develop the best documentary projects, connect them with potential partners and help them.','<p>Implementation of electronic document management system.</p><p>Electronic document management system \"InDocs\" will allow you to automate all the paperwork processes in the company in a short time. Reduce expenses both in time and money for internal workflow. In comparison with paper workflow it allows to completely exclude facts of documents loss, long waiting for managers\' signatures, resolutions not clear for executors, to decrease expenses for paper, to tie up efficiency of the system to KPI of each employee and manager.</p>',136,'en'),(775,'PhonerLite','Is a light and simple application for Windows. PhonerLite allows your PC to be used for internet telephony (VoIP, voice over IP). Requires a full-duplex sound card, microphone and speakers (or headphones), and an internet connection.','<p>Phoner: There is an application called Phoner with which PhonerLite shares a common source code and \"sipper.dll\" file. All VoIP specific configurations are the same and can be used in both Phoner and PhonerLite without conversions If Phoner and PhonerLite are installed in the same directory, they use the same DLL and configuration data (sipper.ini). The main difference is that PhonerLite uses a different GUI interface than Phoner.</p><p>Lite: Just like Coke light, the epithet light implies a light version of the original product. PhonerLite does not save calories, but it does save resources, in our case RAM. PhonerLite is much easier to use than Phoner. This advantage also has disadvantages: no answering machine and no text-to-speech (TTS).</p>',209,'en'),(776,'Yealink','Yealink equipment has passed tests for compatibility with communication platforms, call center platforms and virtual PBXs from the world\'s leading developers (Broadsoft, 3CX, Oktell, Asterisk, MTA, Agat-RT and more than 80 others).','<p>Founded in 2001, Yealink Network Technology is a leading global manufacturer of subscriber equipment for IP telephony and video conferencing. Yealink\'s focus is entirely on IP communications, so the company\'s products are of high quality, reliable, easy to deploy and affordable price. Today, customers in all industries in more than 140 countries choose Yealink equipment to enhance the reliability, quality and ergonomics of communication networks.</p>',211,'en'),(777,'Yeastar','High achievement under this program confirms a partner\'s professionalism and competence. Moreover, employees of Silver Partners (and above) are required to have special certificates confirming technical competence.','<p>Yeastar Information Technology has been developing and manufacturing hybrid IP-PBXs and VoIP-gateways since 2006, constantly working on improving its products to meet the next generation of communication technologies. Yeastar creates cost-effective solutions for small and medium-sized offices that combine all necessary standards and communication protocols. This suite allows for unparalleled versatility and flexibility in the telecommunications solution. The company is one of the world\'s recognized PBX manufacturers and has established itself as a reliable and technologically advanced partner.</p>',212,'en'),(778,'Doc